summary: An Ordinance amending Section 2, 3 and 4 of Ordinance No. 20088 entitled "An Ordinance granting to the Seattle, Renton & Southern Railway Company, its successors and assigns, a franchise to construct, maintain and operate street railways upon Genesee Street, Fiftieth Avenue South, Hudson Street, Thirty-fifth Avenue South, and other streets, avenues and places in the City of Seattle," approved February 2, 1909, and accepted February 26, 1909.
